---

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pour a good glug of @oil{for roasting} onto a #baking tray{} and pop in your oven. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil on high heat with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Peel the @potatoes{450%g}, chop into 4cm chunks. Simmer them in the boiling water until the edges have softened when you poke them with a knife, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Drain in a #colander{}, pop back into the pan, sprinkle on half the @ground turmeric{1%tsp} and half the @mustard seeds{1%tsp}. Give your pan a shake to fluff up the potato. Take your hot baking tray out of your oven, carefully transfer your potatoes onto it in a single layer, turning in the oil. Season with @salt{}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}, turning halfway.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @ginger{1/2%inch piece}(peeled and grated). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @mint{1%handful} leaves from their stalks (discard the stalks). Roughly chop the @coriander{1%handful}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Halve the @lemon{1/2}(halved). Pop the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} into a #food processor{} with the coriander, mint leaves, half the ginger, @sugar{} and a squeeze of lemon juice and blitz to a smooth sauce. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

> TIP: If you don't have a food processor, finely chop the herbs then mix them with the yoghurt, ginger, sugar and lemon juice.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{for frying} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the onion. Cook, stirring, until soft and slightly browned, ~{6-8%minutes}. Add the garlic, remaining ginger, half the @North Indian style spice mix{1%tsp}, remaining turmeric and mustard seeds. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @chopped cavolo nero{200%g} and cook, stirring frequently, for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of water and cover with a #lid{} (or some #foil{}). Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat, cover and keep warm.

Pop the @monkfish medallions{200%g} into a medium #mixing bowl{} with the remaining curry powder and a drizzle of @oil{for coating}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix well to coat. Heat a drizzle of @oil{for cooking} in a frying pan on high heat. When hot, add the monkfish pieces. Cook them until browned and cooked through, ~{3%minutes} each side, adjust the heat if necessary. IMPORTANT: The monkfish is cooked when opaque in the centre. When cooked, transfer to a #plate{} and keep warm but don't wash up the pan!

Reheat the cavolo nero if you need to. Add the @mango chutney{40%g} to the monkfish pan with a splash of water over low to medium heat and simmer for ~{30%seconds} until sticky but with a pourable consistency. Divide the roast potatoes, cavolo nero and monkfish between plates, spoon the mango glaze over the monkfish and serve with the herby yoghurt sauce. Enjoy!